{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780205029954,"sessionID":"ses_183832656ffeoAakJrM2UesW0p","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_function_ocyejuzxh13h_1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Phase 002: Implementation deep research (multi-model)\"\n3: description: \"GPT-5.5-primary (xhigh-fast, cli-codex) implementation deep research with Opus 4.8 agent verification + synthesis, turning the converged 001 design into a build-ready implementation playbook for the deep-improvement rename + Lane C (skill-benchmark).\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"implementation deep research\"\n6:   - \"122 phase 002\"\n7:   - \"deep-improvement implementation playbook\"\n8: importance_tier: \"important\"\n9: contextType: \"research\"\n10: _memory:\n11:   continuity:\n12:     packet_pointer: \"skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research\"\n13:     last_updated_at: \"2026-05-30T00:00:00Z\"\n14:     last_updated_by: \"claude-opus\"\n15:     recent_action: \"GPT-5.5 sweep done 5/5; dual Opus verification; playbook synthesized\"\n16:     next_safe_action: \"Begin Phase 003 narrow rename; checkpoint operator before shared advisor edits\"\n17:     blockers: []\n18:     completion_pct: 100\n19:     open_questions: []\n20:     answered_questions: []\n21: ---\n22: <!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: spec-core | v2.2 -->\n23: <!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 2 -->\n24: \n25: # Phase 002 — Implementation deep research\n26: \n27: **Parent:** `122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode`\n28: **Type:** Deep-research phase (turns the converged 001 design into a build-ready implementation playbook)\n29: **Status:** Complete — GPT-5.5 sweep + Opus verification done; `research/research.md` synthesized\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## 1. Purpose\n34: \n35: Run a GPT-5.5-primary deep-research loop (with Opus 4.8 agent verification) to determine the best WAY TO IMPLEMENT the `deep-agent-improvement` → `deep-improvement` rename and Lane C (\"skill-benchmark\"). Phase 001 converged the DESIGN (what to measure, scoring, harness, fixtures, report, rename impact map); this phase produces the build-ready IMPLEMENTATION PLAYBOOK consumed by Phase 003 (rename) and Phase 004 (Lane C build).\n36: \n37: Research only — no implementation. Report findings, cite sources, never implement fixes during research.\n38: \n39: ## 2. Implementation research questions\n40: \n41: - **IQ1.** Lane C module architecture & seam reuse within the FIXED per-lane layout (`skill-benchmark/` subdir under `assets/`/`references/`/`scripts/` + `shared/`): what is genuinely shared vs Lane-C-specific, and how much of Lane B's scorer/grader/cache + `dispatch-model.cjs` to reuse vs fork.\n42: - **IQ2.** How to wire `scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs --mode=skill-benchmark` (materialize → dispatch → score → report) while keeping Lane A/B byte-identical when the flag is absent (the TST-1 identity contract).\n43: - **IQ3.** Trace-capture implementation: fidelity tier to build first; parse ALL file-touch verbs (Read, Bash cat/rg, Grep, Glob) across all 5 executors; canonicalize to resource keys; golden-trace fixture.\n44: - **IQ4.** Router-replay (Mode A, pure route function) + live (Mode B) implementation; out-of-band `advisor_recommend` capture for the D1 inter-skill signal; the A↔B divergence finding.\n45: - **IQ5.** Contamination linter (reusing the routers' own substring logic) + the 3-tier fixture pipeline (T1 auto+paraphrased / T2 hand-authored holdout / T3 adversarial) + public/private schema + T1↔T2 circularity meter + coverage assertion.\n46: - **IQ6.** Scorer + report-builder: D1–D5 computation reusing Lane B shapes; render `report.md` FROM `report.json`; bottleneck ranking by funnel attrition; remediation taxonomy.\n47: - **IQ7.** Rename execution runbook from the 001 impact map (atomic advisor TS+Python update, index-regen LAST, validation gate) + resolve the 4 decision-record items (agent identity; `deep-model-benchmark` alias; command verbs [keep]; narrow-vs-wide [operator chose NARROW]).\n48: - **IQ8.** Pilot skills to dogfood Lane C on first; weight/verdict-band calibration; vitest/integration test patterns for the new lane; external prior art for harness implementation.\n49: \n50: ## 3. Method — GPT-5.5 primary, Opus verify (operator doctrine)\n51: \n52: GPT-5.5 xhigh-fast (`cli-codex`) is the primary research executor; **Opus 4.8 agents verify the findings and synthesize the playbook.** Generation runs via the packet-local background worker pool (mirrors Phase 001): `cat jobs.txt | xargs -P 2 -L 1 ./run_one.sh`, each iteration a LEAF `@deep-research` pass writing its own packet; a salvage fallback recovers replies when the sandbox blocks the in-repo write.\n53: \n54: | Stage | Executor | Role |\n55: | ----- | -------- | ---- |\n56: | Generation — 5 iterations | `cli-codex` `gpt-5.5`, `model_reasoning_effort=xhigh`, `service_tier=fast` | Run the 5 IQ-focused research iterations |\n57: | Verification + synthesis | Opus 4.8 (native Agent) | Adversarially verify findings, then synthesize `research/research.md` |\n58: \n59: Per-iteration foci: iter1 = IQ1 + IQ8; iter2 = IQ2 + IQ3; iter3 = IQ4 + IQ5; iter4 = IQ6; iter5 = IQ7.\n60: \n61: Per the CLI dispatch rule, `cli-codex/SKILL.md` is read before composing executor prompts.\n62: \n63: ## 4. Deliverables\n64: \n65: - `research/research.md` — Opus-synthesized, build-ready implementation playbook answering IQ1–IQ8, with a Cross-checks section recording the Opus verification verdicts.\n66: - `research/gpt55/iterations/iteration-00{1..5}.md` — 5 GPT-5.5 iteration narratives.\n67: - `research/gpt55/{deltas,state-parts}/*.jsonl` — per-iteration findings + state.\n68: - `research/orchestration-status.log` — per-iteration driver ledger.\n69: \n70: ## 5. Success criteria\n71: \n72: - 5/5 GPT-5.5 iteration artifacts present; `orchestration-status.log` shows every iteration `exit=0`; the Opus verification pass is complete.\n73: - `research/research.md` answers each IQ with cited sources and a concrete shared-vs-skill-benchmark module map + rename runbook.\n74: - The 4 rename decision-record items are resolved (including a documented narrow-vs-wide recommendation).\n75: - Findings are concrete enough to drive Phase 003 (rename) and Phase 004 (Lane C build).\n76: \n77: ## 6. Out of scope\n78: \n79: No implementation, no rename execution, no Lane C build, no skill mutation, no change to the fixed per-lane directory layout or the fixed (narrow) rename scope. This phase produces evidence and a build playbook only.\n\n(End of file - total 79 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Phase 002: Implementation deep research (multi-model)\"\ndescription: \"GPT-5.5-primary (xhigh-fast, cli-codex) implementation deep research with Opus 4.8 agent verification + synthesis, turning the converged 001 design into a build-ready implementation playbook for the deep-improvement rename + Lane C (skill-benchmark).\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"implementation deep research\"\n  - \"122 phase 002\"\n  - \"deep-improvement implementation playbook\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"research\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \"skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-05-30T00:00:00Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude-opus\"\n    recent_action: \"GPT-5.5 sweep done 5/5; dual Opus verification; playbook synthesized\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Begin Phase 003 narrow rename; checkpoint operator before shared advisor edits\"\n    blockers: []\n    completion_pct: 100\n    open_questions: []\n    answered_questions: []","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/spec.md","time":{"start":1780205029936,"end":1780205029952}},"id":"prt_e7c7d0865001OLf0y1nDJTVz6g","sessionID":"ses_183832656ffeoAakJrM2UesW0p","messageID":"msg_e7c7cff53001oxAWKAb3ofPsl1"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780205030815,"sessionID":"ses_183832656ffeoAakJrM2UesW0p","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_function_ocyejuzxh13h_2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/003-skill-rename-deep-improvement/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/003-skill-rename-deep-improvement/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Phase 003: Rename deep-agent-improvement to deep-improvement\"\n3: description: \"Rename the deep-agent-improvement skill to deep-improvement across skill dir, SKILL.md, commands, agent + runtime mirrors, advisor graph, descriptions.json, and cross-references; zero dangling refs; green advisor rebuild.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep-improvement rename\"\n6:   - \"122 phase 003\"\n7:   - \"rename deep-agent-improvement\"\n8: importance_tier: \"important\"\n9: contextType: \"implementation\"\n10: _memory:\n11:   continuity:\n12:     packet_pointer: \"skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/003-skill-rename-deep-improvement\"\n13:     last_updated_at: \"2026-05-30T00:00:00Z\"\n14:     last_updated_by: \"claude-opus\"\n15:     recent_action: \"Narrow rename completed (Opus finished advisor after codex partial); audited clean\"\n16:     next_safe_action: \"Commit the rename scoped to the surface, then begin Phase 004 Lane C build\"\n17:     blockers: []\n18:     completion_pct: 100\n19:     open_questions: []\n20:     answered_questions: []\n21: ---\n22: <!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: spec-core | v2.2 -->\n23: <!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 2 -->\n24: \n25: # Phase 003 — Rename deep-agent-improvement → deep-improvement\n26: \n27: **Parent:** `122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode`\n28: **Type:** Implementation (rename / refactor)\n29: **Status:** Complete — narrow rename done + Opus-audited clean.\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## 1. Purpose\n34: \n35: Rename the skill `deep-agent-improvement` to `deep-improvement` across every surface so the name reflects its real scope (agents + models + skills). The `-agent-` infix is now misleading.\n36: \n37: ## 2. Scope (surface list — confirmed/expanded by Phase 001 RQ6)\n38: \n39: - `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/` → `.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/` (dir + `SKILL.md` `name:`/frontmatter/triggers/keywords).\n40: - Commands referencing the skill path: `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop`, `/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop` (and the new `/deep:start-skill-benchmark-loop`) — update skill-path references. **Command verbs are NOT renamed** unless Phase 001 shows a reason; the agent-improvement command still improves agents.\n41: - Agent file `.opencode/agents/deep-agent-improvement.md` + runtime mirrors `.claude/agents/`, `.codex/agents/`, `.gemini/agents/`.\n42: - Skill-advisor graph (`system-skill-advisor/.../skill-graph.json`), `descriptions.json`, advisor metadata; run advisor rebuild.\n43: - Cross-references: sentinel `sk-prompt-models`, root `CLAUDE.md` / `AGENTS.md` agent-routing entries, any other skills/docs that name `deep-agent-improvement`.\n44: - Internal self-references inside the skill's own references/scripts/README.\n45: \n46: ## 3. Approach\n47: \n48: Use `git mv` for the directory to preserve history; then a tracked find-and-replace across the confirmed surface list; then advisor rebuild + validate. Agent-name decision (`@deep-agent-improvement` → `@deep-improvement`?) recorded explicitly in this phase's `decision-record.md`.\n49: \n50: ## 4. Success criteria\n51: \n52: - Zero dangling `deep-agent-improvement` references where `deep-improvement` is intended (grep-clean, allowing intentional historical mentions in archives).\n53: - Skill-advisor rebuild + `advisor_validate` green; skill resolvable under the new name.\n54: - Lane A (`/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop`) and Lane B (`/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop`) still run.\n55: - `validate.sh --strict` green for this phase.\n56: \n57: ## 5. Out of scope\n58: \n59: Lane C build (Phase 004); doc/README three-lane rewrite beyond what the rename requires (Phase 005).\n\n(End of file - total 59 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Phase 003: Rename deep-agent-improvement to deep-improvement\"\ndescription: \"Rename the deep-agent-improvement skill to deep-improvement across skill dir, SKILL.md, commands, agent + runtime mirrors, advisor graph, descriptions.json, and cross-references; zero dangling refs; green advisor rebuild.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep-improvement rename\"\n  - \"122 phase 003\"\n  - \"rename deep-agent-improvement\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \"skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/003-skill-rename-deep-improvement\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-05-30T00:00:00Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude-opus\"\n    recent_action: \"Narrow rename completed (Opus finished advisor after codex partial); audited clean\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Commit the rename scoped to the surface, then begin Phase 004 Lane C build\"\n    blockers: []\n    completion_pct: 100\n    open_questions: []\n    answered_questions: []","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/003-skill-rename-deep-improvement/spec.md","time":{"start":1780205030793,"end":1780205030814}},"id":"prt_e7c7d0a340012vQeS4vDTHoatZ","sessionID":"ses_183832656ffeoAakJrM2UesW0p","messageID":"msg_e7c7cff53001oxAWKAb3ofPsl1"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780205031337,"sessionID":"ses_183832656ffeoAakJrM2UesW0p","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_function_ocyejuzxh13h_3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/004-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/004-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Phase 004: Skill-benchmark mode (Lane C) design + build\"\n3: description: \"Design and build Lane C (skill-benchmark) in the renamed deep-improvement skill: scenario fixtures, hint-free dispatcher capturing resource-load traces, routing/discovery/efficiency/usefulness scorer, ranked remediation report, and /deep:start-skill-benchmark-loop command.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"skill-benchmark mode build\"\n6:   - \"122 phase 004\"\n7:   - \"Lane C skill benchmark\"\n8: importance_tier: \"important\"\n9: contextType: \"implementation\"\n10: _memory:\n11:   continuity:\n12:     packet_pointer: \"skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/004-skill-benchmark-mode\"\n13:     last_updated_at: \"2026-05-30T00:00:00Z\"\n14:     last_updated_by: \"claude-opus\"\n15:     recent_action: \"Built Lane C Mode A spine + 14 tests; runs end-to-end; Opus reviewed\"\n16:     next_safe_action: \"Phase 005 three-lane docs + hardening; then Mode B live dispatch\"\n17:     blockers: []\n18:     completion_pct: 100\n19:     open_questions: []\n20:     answered_questions: []\n21: ---\n22: <!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: spec-core | v2.2 -->\n23: <!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 3 -->\n24: \n25: # Phase 004 — Skill-benchmark mode (Lane C): design + build\n26: \n27: **Parent:** `122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode`\n28: **Type:** Implementation (new lane)\n29: **Status:** Mode A spine complete + verified; D1-inter/D4 deferred to live mode\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## 1. Purpose\n34: \n35: Design and build **Lane C (skill-benchmark)** in the renamed `deep-improvement` skill: a benchmark that measures whether a *skill* is well-structured, well-routed, efficient, and useful **in practice** (how AIs actually discover/use it), and emits actionable, ranked remediation findings.\n36: \n37: The converged design from Phase 001 is authoritative, and the Phase 002 implementation playbook is the build guide; this spec is the working frame.\n38: \n39: ## 2. Build (reusing the three pluggable seams)\n40: \n41: - **Fixtures (candidate-source).** Per-target-skill scenario set: realistic prompt + expected activation + expected reference/asset(s) + correct-outcome rubric, including negatives (should-not-activate). Authoring approach per Phase 001 RQ4.\n42: - **Dispatcher.** Hint-free harness (Phase 001 RQ2) that runs each scenario against an executor and captures the resource-load trace + tool trace (what was opened, order, call count). Model-agnostic, reusing the Lane B executor-routing map.\n43: - **Scorer.** Compare actual vs expected across the dimensions confirmed in Phase 001 (routing/activation accuracy, unprompted discovery precision/recall, efficiency/bottlenecks, usefulness ablation, structural connectivity). Reuse the Lane B deterministic-checks + pluggable-grader shape.\n44: - **Mode.** `scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs --mode=skill-benchmark`; records carry `mode: skill-benchmark`; report carries `scoringMethod`. Lane A/B remain byte-identical when the flag is absent.\n45: - **Command.** `/deep:start-skill-benchmark-loop` (`:auto`/`:confirm`). Reuse the model-benchmark command scaffold unless Phase 001 RQ6 says otherwise.\n46: - **Report.** Skill Benchmark Report: per-dimension scores + ranked bottlenecks + concrete remediations (Phase 001 RQ5). Diagnostic by default (no target-skill mutation); optional hand-off to Lane A.\n47: \n48: ## 3. Resources to add\n49: \n50: - `references/skill-benchmark/*` (operator guide, evaluator/scoring contract, scenario-authoring guide).\n51: - `assets/skill-benchmark/*` (scenario-fixture schema, report template, default profile).\n52: - `scripts/skill-benchmark/*` (dispatch capture, scorer, report builder) + loop-host mode wiring.\n53: \n54: Per the fixed per-lane layout: Lane C adds exactly one subdir per area (`skill-benchmark/`) under `references/`/`assets/`/`scripts/`; genuinely cross-lane logic goes in `shared/`. The Phase 002 playbook fixes the shared-vs-Lane-C module split.\n55: \n56: ## 4. Success criteria\n57: \n58: - Lane C runs end-to-end on ≥1 real target skill and emits a ranked, actionable Skill Benchmark Report.\n59: - Lane A/B behavior unchanged without the mode flag (regression check).\n60: - Repeatability evidence (variance across runs) is captured, mirroring Lane B stability.\n61: - `validate.sh --strict` green for this phase.\n62: \n63: ## 5. Out of scope\n64: \n65: Remediating flagged skills (NG1). Replacing `sk-doc` validation or manual playbooks (NG2). `deep-loop-runtime` changes (NG3).\n\n(End of file - total 65 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Phase 004: Skill-benchmark mode (Lane C) design + build\"\ndescription: \"Design and build Lane C (skill-benchmark) in the renamed deep-improvement skill: scenario fixtures, hint-free dispatcher capturing resource-load traces, routing/discovery/efficiency/usefulness scorer, ranked remediation report, and /deep:start-skill-benchmark-loop command.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"skill-benchmark mode build\"\n  - \"122 phase 004\"\n  - \"Lane C skill benchmark\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \"skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/004-skill-benchmark-mode\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-05-30T00:00:00Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude-opus\"\n    recent_action: \"Built Lane C Mode A spine + 14 tests; runs end-to-end; Opus reviewed\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Phase 005 three-lane docs + hardening; then Mode B live dispatch\"\n    blockers: []\n    completion_pct: 100\n    open_questions: []\n    answered_questions: []","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/004-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md","time":{"start":1780205031320,"end":1780205031336}},"id":"prt_e7c7d0d8e001a9QpoIZtbbDmjr","sessionID":"ses_183832656ffeoAakJrM2UesW0p","messageID":"msg_e7c7cff53001oxAWKAb3ofPsl1"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780205031511,"sessionID":"ses_183832656ffeoAakJrM2UesW0p","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_function_ocyejuzxh13h_4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/005-validation-and-docs/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/005-validation-and-docs/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Phase 005: Validation & docs (three-lane)\"\n3: description: \"Bring SKILL.md, README, catalog, and advisor metadata up to the three-lane (agent-improvement / model-benchmark / skill-benchmark) reality of the renamed deep-improvement skill; run hardening/deep-review gate; end-to-end validation.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep-improvement three-lane docs\"\n6:   - \"122 phase 005\"\n7:   - \"skill-benchmark validation docs\"\n8: importance_tier: \"normal\"\n9: contextType: \"implementation\"\n10: _memory:\n11:   continuity:\n12:     packet_pointer: \"skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/005-validation-and-docs\"\n13:     last_updated_at: \"2026-05-30T00:00:00Z\"\n14:     last_updated_by: \"claude-opus\"\n15:     recent_action: \"Three-lane docs + catalog complete; Opus hardening gate SHIP (208/208, 0 P0/P1)\"\n16:     next_safe_action: \"Packet complete; optional follow-on: D4 ablation + Mode B live trace\"\n17:     blockers: []\n18:     completion_pct: 100\n19:     open_questions: []\n20:     answered_questions: []\n21: ---\n22: <!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: spec-core | v2.2 -->\n23: <!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 1 -->\n24: \n25: # Phase 005 — Validation & docs (three-lane)\n26: \n27: **Parent:** `122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode`\n28: **Type:** Docs + hardening/validation\n29: **Status:** Complete — three-lane docs (SKILL.md, README, feature catalog) + advisor routing + Opus hardening gate (SHIP, 0 P0/P1)\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## 1. Purpose\n34: \n35: Bring all documentation and metadata up to the three-lane (A: agent-improvement, B: model-benchmark, C: skill-benchmark) reality of the renamed `deep-improvement` skill, and run the hardening/deep-review gate.\n36: \n37: ## 2. Scope\n38: \n39: - `deep-improvement/SKILL.md`: two-lane → three-lane (WHEN-TO-USE table, smart-router intents/RESOURCE_MAP for `skill-benchmark`, lane-aware references/assets, integration points).\n40: - `README.md` + skill catalog/playbook/advisor labels: add Lane C.\n41: - `descriptions.json` + skill-advisor graph: reflect Lane C command + skill name.\n42: - Cross-skill references (sentinel, root docs) consistent with the rename + new lane.\n43: - Hardening/deep-review: run `/deep:start-review-loop` (or equivalent) over the new Lane C code; fix findings.\n44: \n45: ## 3. Success criteria\n46: \n47: - Docs accurately describe three lanes; no two-lane-only stragglers.\n48: - Advisor rebuild + validate green; Lane C discoverable via advisor.\n49: - Deep-review findings triaged/fixed.\n50: - `validate.sh --strict` green for parent + all active children.\n51: - Completion metadata reconciled across parent `spec.md`, child docs, and continuity.\n52: \n53: ## 4. Out of scope\n54: \n55: New feature work beyond documenting/hardening Lanes A/B/C.\n\n(End of file - total 55 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Phase 005: Validation & docs (three-lane)\"\ndescription: \"Bring SKILL.md, README, catalog, and advisor metadata up to the three-lane (agent-improvement / model-benchmark / skill-benchmark) reality of the renamed deep-improvement skill; run hardening/deep-review gate; end-to-end validation.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep-improvement three-lane docs\"\n  - \"122 phase 005\"\n  - \"skill-benchmark validation docs\"\nimportance_tier: \"normal\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \"skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/005-validation-and-docs\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-05-30T00:00:00Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude-opus\"\n    recent_action: \"Three-lane docs + catalog complete; Opus hardening gate SHIP (208/208, 0 P0/P1)\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Packet complete; optional follow-on: D4 ablation + Mode B live trace\"\n    blockers: []\n    completion_pct: 100\n    open_questions: []\n    answered_questions: []","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/005-validation-and-docs/spec.md","time":{"start":1780205031489,"end":1780205031510}},"id":"prt_e7c7d0f9b0018o79A71V8p0rw6","sessionID":"ses_183832656ffeoAakJrM2UesW0p","messageID":"msg_e7c7cff53001oxAWKAb3ofPsl1"}}
